                "invention-title": "HYDROGEN PRODUCTION METHOD"
            },
            "abstract": {
                "p": "&lt;P&gt;PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a hydrogen production method by which the production efficiency of hydrogen is improved with the use of ultraviolet ray having increased energy and hydrogen and oxygen are simply separated and recovered from each other. &lt;P&gt;SOLUTION: In the production of hydrogen by a photochemical reaction by irradiating water and a photocatalyst with light, deep ultraviolet ray is emitted as the light. An optical fiber 1 or an optical pipe 5 to which fluorine having small deep ultraviolet ray absorption is added is used in the irradiation with the deep ultraviolet ray. In the use of the optical fiber 1, the deep ultraviolet ray is leaked and emitted in the outside of the optical fiber by passing water on the outside part of the optical fiber 1. In the use of the optical pipe 5, water is passed along the inside of the pipe 5 to leak and emit the deep ultraviolet ray inside the pipe 5. In this way by irradiating with the deep ultraviolet ray having high energy, hydrogen is produced with high efficiency. &lt;P&gt;COPYRIGHT: (C)2004,JPO&NCIPI"
